PORT=4000
OPENAI_API_KEY="your_openai_api_key_here"
OPENAI_BASE_URL="http://localhost:port/v1"
OPENAI_MODEL="gpt-5.2"
DIDA_CLIENT_ID=your_dida_client_id_here
DIDA_CLIENT_SECRET=your_dida_client_secret_here
DIDA_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:36500/oauth/callback"
TIME_SOURCE="Local"
# TIME_SOURCE="Asia/Shanghai"
AI_TASK_SYSTEM_HINT="You specialize in turning Markdown checklists into JSON tasks. Preserve the original language, keep titles concise, and provide actionable suggestions as bullet points (one per line) inside the description field. Mirror the checkbox completion status using a boolean named completed. Always analyze the provided project list and pick the most suitable projectId for every task (use an empty string only when no projects are available). For scheduling, judge whether the task is a time point or a time span: use only dueDate for point tasks; use startDate + dueDate for span tasks; date-only values are fine; leave both empty if unsure. If the input already contains explicit or relative dates/times (e.g., 今天/明天/11:00-13:00), map them to ISO 8601 in the appropriate fields using the current_time and default time source; when timezone is missing, keep the date/time and assume the default time source; if only a date is clear, output date-only; if nothing is reliable, leave both empty. Propose priority when helpful; leave it empty if not. Never add commentary outside of the JSON body."
AI_TASK_USER_TEMPLATE='Language: {{locale}}\nCurrent Time: {{current_time}}{{time_hint}}\nGuidelines:\n{{system_hint}}\n\nAvailable Projects (JSON Array):\n{{project_list}}\n\nConvert the following Markdown checklist line into JSON. Each checkbox becomes one entry with title, description (list actionable suggestions, one per line), completed (true for - [x], false for - [ ]), projectId (must come from the project list; use empty string only when the list is empty), and scheduling fields in ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss±HH:MM with timezone offset, e.g., 2024-08-01T10:00:00+08:00). Determine time type: if the text implies a point, provide only dueDate; if it implies a span (e.g., 11:00-13:00), provide startDate and dueDate; date-only is acceptable; if no reliable time is present, leave both empty. Resolve relative dates like 今天/明天/tonight using {{current_time}} and the default time source; when only a date is clear, return date-only; times are optional. Always include timezone offset when time is specified. Include priority when it adds value; otherwise leave it empty. Maintain the original intent and respond with JSON only.\n\nInput:\n{{markdown}}\n\nOutput:\n{"tasks":[{"title":"示例任务","description":"详细说明，保持原始语气并补充分步骤","completed":false,"projectId":"6226ff...","dueDate":"2024-08-01T10:00:00+08:00"}]}'
